import pandas as pd

pd.set_option('display.max_rows', None)
pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)

# Read the CSV file into a DataFrame
df = pd.read_csv('CLEANED UP Sandwich Totals-Sheet1-v59.csv')

# Display the first 5 rows
print(df.head().to_string(index=False))

# Print the column names and their data types
print(df.info())

I'll create the table you requested, listing each donation with the date, host location, and number of sandwiches collected, using the data from your sheet (A1:W266). This will involve transforming the data so that each row represents a single donation from a specific host on a particular date.

Please give me a moment to process the data.

# Identify the date column and the host location columns
date_column = 'Date'
host_location_columns = df.columns[6:23]

# Convert host location columns to numeric, coercing errors to NaN
for col in host_location_columns:
    df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors='coerce')

# Unpivot the DataFrame
melted_df = pd.melt(df,
                    id_vars=[date_column],
                    value_vars=host_location_columns,
                    var_name='Host Location',
                    value_name='Number of Sandwiches')

# Remove rows where 'Number of Sandwiches' is NaN
melted_df = melted_df.dropna(subset=['Number of Sandwiches'])

# Display the resulting table
print(melted_df.head().to_string())
